! Inline Rules — Railroad Diagrams

This tiddler presents the same inline wikitext syntax as [[EBNF - Inline Rules]], but using railroad diagrams for visual clarity. Follow the tracks left-to-right to see valid syntax paths.

!! Emphasis

Six emphasis rules use symmetric markers. Content between the markers is parsed recursively.

!!! Bold

Two single-quote characters wrap content to produce `<strong>`.

<$railroad text=""" "''" <"inline-content"> "''" """/>

!!! Italic

Two forward slashes wrap content to produce `<em>`.

<$railroad text=""" "//" <"inline-content"> "//" """/>

!!! Strikethrough

Two tildes wrap content to produce `<s>`.

<$railroad text=""" "~~" <"inline-content"> "~~" """/>

!!! Superscript

Two carets wrap content to produce `<sup>`.

<$railroad text=""" "^^" <"inline-content"> "^^" """/>

!!! Subscript

Two commas wrap content to produce `<sub>`.

<$railroad text=""" ",," <"inline-content"> ",," """/>

!!! Underscore

Two underscores wrap content to produce `<u>`.

<$railroad text=""" "__" <"inline-content"> "__" """/>

!! Code Inline

Backtick-delimited code. Content is ''not'' parsed — it is raw text. The closing marker must match the opening (single or double backtick).

<$railroad text=""" ("`" <"raw-text"> "`" | "``" <"raw-text"> "``") """/>

!! Formatting

!!! Dash

Two or three hyphens (not followed by another hyphen) produce an en-dash or em-dash.

<$railroad text=""" ("---" / "em-dash" / | "--" / "en-dash" /) """/>

!!! Entity

HTML entities — named (`&copy;`) or numeric (`&#169;`).

<$railroad text=""" "&" ["#"] <"name 2-8 chars"> ";" """/>

!!! Style Inline

Inline styling with `@@`. Optional CSS declarations and/or dot-prefixed class names, then content, closed by `@@`.

<$railroad text=""" "@@" [{:"property:value;"}] [{:"." <"class-name">}] <"inline-content"> "@@" """/>

!! Links

!!! ~WikiLink

CamelCase words auto-link. Prefix with `~` to suppress.

<$railroad text=""" ["~" / "suppresses link" /] <"CamelCaseWord"> """/>

!!! Pretty Link

Double square brackets with optional display text.

<$railroad text=""" "[[" <"display-text"> ["|"] <"target"> "]]" """/>

!!! System Link

System tiddler references starting with `$:/` auto-link. Prefix with `~` to suppress.

<$railroad text=""" ["~"] "$:/" <"path-chars"> """/>

!!! External Link

Bare URLs with recognised protocols auto-link. Prefix with `~` to suppress.

<$railroad text=""" ["~"] ("http" | "https" | "file" | "mailto" | "ftp" | "irc" | "news" | "data" | "skype") ":" <"url-chars"> """/>

!!! Pretty External Link

Explicit external link with optional display text.

<$railroad text=""" "[ext[" <"display-text"> ["|"] <"url"> "]]" """/>

!! Images

The `[img` prefix, optional attributes, then the source in brackets. An optional tooltip is separated by `|`.

<$railroad text=""" "[img" [{<"attribute">}] "[" [<"tooltip"> "|"] <"source"> "]]" """/>

!! Comments

HTML comment syntax. Everything between `<!--` and `-->` is consumed and not rendered.

<$railroad text=""" "<!--" <"comment-text"> "-->" """/>

!! Conditional (inline form)

Filter-based conditional branching within inline text. The filter is evaluated at runtime — any output means true.

<$railroad text=""" "<%if" <"filter-expr"> "%>" <"inline-content"> [{"<%elseif" <"filter-expr"> "%>" <"inline-content">}] ["<%else%>" <"inline-content">] "<%endif%>" """/>

!! Hard Line Breaks

Within `"""` delimiters, every newline becomes a `<br>`. Inline formatting is still parsed.

<$railroad text=` '"""' {<"inline-content"> / "newline becomes br" /} '"""' `/>
